 fusioned and factors that bias their collection processes are\nproperly accounted for. The study of powerline-induced deaths shows a clear\nassociation between the density of the powerline network and the risk that\npowerlines represent for bird populations. The choice of model is relevant for\nthe conclusions from this case study as different models estimated the\nassociation between risk of powerline-induced deaths and the amount of exposed\nbirds differently.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Mar 2023 17:04:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-06"}
